        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>MR_DistanceMapSaveSettings</name>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>determines how to save distance maps Generated from class <computeroutput>MR::DistanceMapSaveSettings</computeroutput>. Supported <computeroutput>MR_PassBy</computeroutput> modes: <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultConstruct</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Copy</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Move</computeroutput> (and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultArgument</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_NoObject</computeroutput> if supported by the callee). Cartesian range vector between distance map borders in X direction Returns a pointer to a member variable of class <computeroutput>MR::MeshToDistanceMapParams</computeroutput> named <computeroutput>xRange</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>_this</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. The returned pointer will never be null. It is non-owning, do NOT destroy it. The reference to this object might be preserved as the return value. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
